+Build the production jar:
+
+```bash
+sbt assembly
+```
+
+Run one MBA basic-income counterfactual point from the normal jar entrypoint:
+
+```bash
+java -jar target/scala-3.8.2/amor-fati.jar 10 bdp-2000 --duration 60 --run-id bdp-2000-60m-10s --bdp 2000
+```
+
+For a sweep, run the jar once per BDP level with the same seed count and
+duration. Downstream Python scripts can compare the generated `mc/` files across
+output prefixes such as `bdp-0000`, `bdp-0500`, and `bdp-2000`.
+BDP runs use the central reservation-wage pass-through assumption `lambda=0.5`
+by default. Override it with `--bdp-lambda <0..1>` for robustness checks; baseline
+runs without `--bdp` or with `--bdp 0` leave the baseline parameters unchanged.
+
+```bash
+java -jar target/scala-3.8.2/amor-fati.jar 10 bdp-2000-lambda-075 \
+  --duration 60 --run-id bdp-2000-lambda-075-60m-10s --bdp 2000 --bdp-lambda 0.75
+```
+
 Robustness scenario sets come from
 `src/main/scala/com/boombustgroup/amorfati/config/RobustnessScenarios.scala` and
 are documented in
